WEBVTT

00:00:00.400 --> 00:00:12.178
Wow, that was fast. Well, good evening everybody. Thank you for joining us tonight. I don't know where Braden wants to go from here.

00:00:12.179 --> 00:00:24.399
I've got my microphone, but I had a really interesting conversation yesterday on the phone.

00:00:24.400 --> 00:00:30.943
Every year, I evaluate where we are, what the Lord has done, and what we could do better.

00:00:30.944 --> 00:00:44.197
Especially now that we're in ministry, I evaluate the intimacy level—checking your thermostat, as I call it. Where is your thermostat with God? How are things?

00:00:44.197 --> 00:01:14.457
If you were to get your report card or your evaluation at work for how you did for the year—your review for the year—and the boss comes in and says, 'Well, you could have done this better, or you did this really well, and your progress report was pretty good, so we'll give you a raise or keep you where you are.'I go over things with the Father like that all the time at the end of the year.

00:01:14.458 --> 00:01:27.243
I always evaluate and write things down because I don't want to be where I am at this time next year. I look and see if I made any progress spiritually.

00:01:27.244 --> 00:01:52.158
After I had a really interesting conversation with a mega-minister yesterday—he called and wanted to talk to me—I asked some questions that I normally don't ask, but the Lord told me to ask him because he would have the answers.

00:01:52.159 --> 00:02:06.265
I asked about a lot of mega-prophets and how come they didn't sustain in ministry or why they went home early.

00:02:06.266 --> 00:02:13.299
I asked what happened to some of these prophetic voices that have gone before us.

00:02:13.300 --> 00:02:32.529
He went over the details of why some of these major voices that used to be—that are no more—fell, and why their ministries faltered.

00:02:32.530 --> 00:02:42.238
He knew a lot of the answers. As we were talking, it really bothered me.

00:02:42.239 --> 00:03:00.916
One person was messed up with homosexuality. One was messing around with golden idols.

00:03:00.917 --> 00:03:10.665
There were so many different things. As I heard it all, I paused.

00:03:10.666 --> 00:03:25.860
They all started out really good with great intentions and great intimacy with the Father. You don't get there without intimacy. But what went wrong?

00:03:25.861 --> 00:03:43.489
I'm not going to reveal these men's names, but as I was thinking about people I had looked up to and admired, you see the slow fade after year after year of ministry.

00:03:43.490 --> 00:04:00.451
I didn't get the answer right off. I was praying all last night and seeking the Lord because of the things He's showing me.

00:04:00.452 --> 00:04:22.262
As you're checking your thermostat of where you are with the Father, you have to ask, 'How is my relationship with God?'I don't ever want to be arrogant and say, 'That will never happen to me,'because these people, in my opinion, were the best over the years.

00:04:22.263 --> 00:04:43.613
How do you stay on the right road? How do you self-evaluate? I woke up this morning and the Lord spoke to me in my sleep.

00:04:43.614 --> 00:05:06.317
He said, 'Intimacy is what gets you there with Me, and intimacy is what will keep you there.'So many times, these ministers start with healings, demonstrations, and manifestations, but they lose the intimacy with the Father.

00:05:06.317 --> 00:05:19.425
The gift is separate from intimacy. Intimacy is how you got the gift, but it's not how you sustain it.

00:05:19.426 --> 00:05:45.038
Over time, you get so caught up—because it's trying to happen to me—with the pulling on the gift that you believe walking underneath that mantle is intimacy for the day.

00:05:45.039 --> 00:05:58.079
You're so busy with all the people pulling on you that you don't separate yourself to have the intimacy that got the gift in the first place.

00:05:58.080 --> 00:06:05.999
It becomes robotic. The Lord said, 'Brandon, it's a slow fade.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:20.959
Many of the ministers you were told about yesterday started out just like you—on fire and effective.

00:06:20.960 --> 00:06:37.599
But the gift and callings of God are without repentance.'You can operate in a gift while there is stuff going on in your personal life because the gift is without repentance.

00:06:37.600 --> 00:07:03.756
You qualify for it, but if you cut yourself off the vine, you don't die instantaneously. Intimacy keeps you on the vine.

00:07:03.757 --> 00:07:19.569
You cannot let intimacy with the Father die, or eventually, your ministry will be short-lived.

00:07:19.570 --> 00:07:26.071
You cannot rely just on the experience of healings and demonstrations.

00:07:26.072 --> 00:07:47.368
I always tell you that covering comes on me and I can feel it when I'm praying, but the Lord was warning me: just because you have that impartation at that time doesn't mean you're walking in intimacy with Me.

00:07:47.369 --> 00:07:55.685
You have to check your spiritual thermostat. They are two different things.

00:07:55.686 --> 00:08:13.442
He's been talking to me about evaluating your progress report. I'm real open about things, and I learn as I go.

00:08:13.443 --> 00:08:31.439
Some of the elders who went before us, like Jack Coe, were warned about their weight. He was in his 30s when he passed away.

00:08:31.440 --> 00:09:20.024
What a tragic thing for somebody who walked in so much creative miracles to only have a ministry last until their 30s. This is so taxing, with so much demand.

00:09:20.025 --> 00:09:42.177
If you keep going down the road—because some people were committing adultery or were homosexual—the Lord warned them, 'If you keep going down this road, you're going to hell.'The word of the Lord came up so strong about this stuff that it shook me.

00:09:42.178 --> 00:09:52.015
I even knew a man personally who was messing around on his wife for two years prior to getting caught.

00:09:52.016 --> 00:10:09.400
The only reason he got caught was a text message. People ask how he kept preaching.

00:10:09.401 --> 00:10:17.175
He said the word is truth regardless. So I'm just preaching the word.

00:10:17.176 --> 00:10:25.540
It's okay; I knew that if I could just keep preaching the word, it didn't matter about my personal life because the word always stands by itself.

00:10:25.541 --> 00:10:32.976
I believe that was it, wasn't it? And I was just thinking that is such a dangerous place to be.

00:10:32.977 --> 00:10:49.088
But just going over your year for 2025 and going into 2026 and looking at what God has for you so that you take what you did well into the year and strip off the bad things.

00:10:49.089 --> 00:11:04.371
And the Lord told me, 'Brandon, I've warned and warned my people.'It keeps stirring up inside of me, what the Lord told me to say about 2026 and 1 Corinthians 5:5.

00:11:04.372 --> 00:11:15.356
As I lay there this morning and listened to the Father, I said, 'God, help me.

00:11:15.357 --> 00:11:20.545
Search me, know me, create in me a clean heart. Strip all this stuff off.

00:11:20.546 --> 00:11:26.683
Whatever it takes, intimacy with Me is more important than anything else.

00:11:26.684 --> 00:11:40.318
Who cares if the platform pulls you away from the Father? If you're so distracted with the platform, then it's time to prune it.

00:11:40.319 --> 00:11:50.665
Does that make sense? He's first. Intimacy is everything to have a relationship—the fellowship that got you there in the first place—to sustain it.

00:11:50.666 --> 00:12:02.950
That's where dryness comes in. There's so much dryness. I see pastors teaching out of their dryness and there's no good word.

00:12:02.951 --> 00:12:18.319
I even talked to one man and he said, 'It's interesting. I can go into a service and they're still preaching on something that they were preaching 30 years ago.

00:12:18.320 --> 00:12:44.719
Thirty years later, they don't have any new wine or new wineskins, continually preaching the same thing.'You get to the point where you ask, 'Do you not have any fresh Rhema from God?'Now, I know Brother Hagin taught Mark 11:23-24, but there was an anointing on it when he preached it.

00:12:44.720 --> 00:12:48.288
You could feel the tangible presence of God when he taught that.

00:12:48.289 --> 00:12:51.869
So obviously, in those cases, it was meant for him to preach.

00:12:51.870 --> 00:13:13.742
Now, for some of these other people, it's like going into the Mojave Desert and wondering, 'Why am I even here?'It's interesting when you talk to people who have been through the trenches, like the person I talked to yesterday and another one of my mentors.

00:13:13.743 --> 00:13:32.199
It's been interesting, the people who have called. You get to meditate on these things and walk away thinking, 'I don't want to say I'll never do that.'I always want to self-evaluate and be humble about it.

00:13:32.200 --> 00:13:39.518
I'm not saying I'm better than them; heavens, no. For some of these people, I couldn't even tie their shoelaces.

00:13:39.519 --> 00:13:48.275
But if you don't self-evaluate your relationship and look at your thermostat with God, you'll drift off easily.

00:13:48.276 --> 00:13:58.958
Just because you have a call and there's a mantle or an impartation on that call doesn't mean that your intimacy level is good.

00:13:58.959 --> 00:14:04.520
You must self-evaluate all the time and say, 'Father, how are you and I?

00:14:04.521 --> 00:14:11.119
Not the ministry. How am I with you? How are things going? Am I doing okay?

00:14:11.120 --> 00:14:20.438
Am I pleasing to you?'After I sat and wept on the floor, He gave me a word. That word was intimacy.

00:14:20.439 --> 00:14:31.356
It was private for me, but I'm very thankful for where I am with my Father. Yes, there are things you can work on.

00:14:31.357 --> 00:14:39.503
Ultimately, if you cut yourself from the vine, you don't instantaneously dry up and die.

00:14:39.504 --> 00:14:52.479
It's a slow fade. You are dying instantaneously, but the branch always has life for a little bit. You can even cut it and see green underneath the bark.

00:14:52.480 --> 00:15:05.494
The leaves start to wither first, the fruit fades, and all of a sudden, what was once alive becomes dead because He's the true source.

00:15:05.495 --> 00:15:13.492
I realized as I listened that I don't want to be a statistic in ministry.

00:15:13.493 --> 00:15:25.077
So as I focus on what could be done better in 2026, I want the capacity to reach the lost to increase.

00:15:25.078 --> 00:15:33.599
The capacity for healing must increase—not just physical healing, but mental and emotional healing.

00:15:33.600 --> 00:15:43.764
There are so many people on our email list dealing with mental drama.

00:15:43.765 --> 00:15:55.935
I try to be a place of refreshing for all people to come and drink from, so that when they are here, they get a fresh touch from the Holy Ghost.

00:15:55.936 --> 00:16:09.605
The only way you can give—'Silver and gold have I none, but such as I have give I thee: In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth rise up and walk'—is through intimacy.

00:16:09.606 --> 00:16:17.070
They had been with Jesus. They were unlearned, uneducated men who had been with Jesus.

00:16:17.071 --> 00:16:25.359
That's what the Bible says. The world marveled because they had been with Jesus.

00:16:25.360 --> 00:16:31.985
It's not just being with Him once; it's being with Him continually, sitting at His feet.

00:16:31.986 --> 00:16:36.709
It's the intimacy with the Father that says, 'Jesus, I'm here.

00:16:36.710 --> 00:16:50.958
I need You to change me and take me from glory to glory.'In Diana's and my case, we practice what we preach when we say we walk in love—sowing even when you don't want to sow, giving and being where God tells you to be.

00:16:50.959 --> 00:16:59.960
It's interesting because we laugh about things. We always say Joyce Meyer talks about how in the kingdom of God, a lot of things are backwards.

00:16:59.961 --> 00:17:06.358
When people treat you badly, you don't go after them or be mean; you walk in love.

00:17:06.359 --> 00:17:11.759
When you sow, you give your money away to believe God for extra.

00:17:11.760 --> 00:17:27.746
Everything seems awkward, upside down, and inside out. We love Joyce Meyer, don't we? Everything goes against your flesh.

00:17:27.747 --> 00:17:43.442
When you think, 'Lord, are You going to release me from this church to move on because of this and that?'and the Lord says, 'No, I want you to stay,'and you keep working things out, it makes your flesh scream.

00:17:43.443 --> 00:17:50.423
If your flesh isn't screaming, you aren't growing spiritually. You need to know this.

00:17:50.424 --> 00:18:02.159
When He says to clean toilets for years, do it with a good heart—without grumbling and complaining.

00:18:02.160 --> 00:18:09.917
Live in a shotgun house for 20 years. Do what I've asked without grumbling and complaining.

00:18:09.918 --> 00:18:18.079
Do all that you do, in word and deed, to the glory of God, and He'll release you.

00:18:18.080 --> 00:18:30.972
Do it with a joyful heart. The willing and obedient will eat the good of the land, not the grudging.

00:18:30.973 --> 00:18:34.904
There are so many times the Lord tells Diana and me to do something against our flesh.

00:18:34.905 --> 00:18:47.888
He says, 'I want you to sow this.'I think, 'Are you kidding me?'But then I say, 'Okay, I'll do it.'But I can't do it with a grudging heart; I have to do it with joy.

00:18:47.889 --> 00:18:57.899
'I love a cheerful giver, Brandon.'So I do it with a cheerful attitude and walk in love.

00:18:57.900 --> 00:19:08.461
This happens to me all the time. The Lord says, 'This is molding you. If you do what I tell you, you'll go to the next level.

00:19:08.462 --> 00:19:25.040
I'm watching your heart.'In a vision, I saw a path of white; it was beautiful but skinny, with no edges.

00:19:25.041 --> 00:19:35.862
As far as the eye could see, it was a dimension. I pulled out of it because it freaked me out.

00:19:35.863 --> 00:19:43.628
I had to meditate on it because the Lord was dealing with me. I saw the nose.

00:19:43.629 --> 00:19:56.677
I saw a cheek, and I saw the side of a mouth. His face was right on the edge of the path, but his eye was all I could see.

00:19:56.678 --> 00:20:01.683
I didn't say this, but he spoke to me in an audible voice in my house.

00:20:01.684 --> 00:20:11.359
That's why it freaked me out. I heard it. And he says, 'I'm watching you.

00:20:11.360 --> 00:20:17.992
I'm watching you.'And that's why I started singing His Eye Is on the Sparrow, for I know he watches me.

00:20:17.993 --> 00:20:24.319
That's why I sang that song because he said to me, 'I'm watching you, Brandon.

00:20:24.320 --> 00:20:29.137
I'm watching you and how you make these decisions and these choices.

00:20:29.138 --> 00:20:39.324
Do you qualify to go to the next level? Do you qualify to get more? I have more in store in 2026.

00:20:39.325 --> 00:20:45.199
I have more in store in the days ahead.'But do you qualify for it?

00:20:45.200 --> 00:20:53.279
What qualifies you? Obedience. Listening whenever your flesh screams.

00:20:53.280 --> 00:20:59.999
Will you qualify, ladies and gentlemen, for what God has for you by obedience?

00:21:00.000 --> 00:21:04.639
Obedience is better than sacrifice. And it's not always easy when he tells you...

00:21:04.640 --> 00:21:12.949
when people call and say, 'I got another call yesterday to go to the White House.'This is the fourth time.

00:21:12.950 --> 00:21:24.983
To go to the White House, fourth time. 'No, don't go. Not yet.''Well, you need to give me an answer.'I could have been there today at the White House.

00:21:24.984 --> 00:21:34.054
It could have been very interesting to meet Jentezen Franklin and Paula White again and another man.

00:21:34.055 --> 00:21:39.324
These people... I always butcher his name, that's why I don't try to say it.

00:21:39.325 --> 00:21:45.918
It's his Spanish name, a pastor from Miami. That's what I say.

00:21:45.919 --> 00:21:50.312
Sorry, I know he's probably watching; I don't mean to be rude.

00:21:50.313 --> 00:22:10.558
It's just I'm not real good with names sometimes, but all the opportunities that come across your path, you're so thankful for what God opens the door maybe, but at the same time, I want to make sure I don't do things without hearing him.

00:22:10.559 --> 00:22:19.111
So I say, I was taught by another prophetic voice: go low, go slow.

00:22:19.112 --> 00:22:23.333
Don't do anything quick. If it needs a quick answer, tell them no.

00:22:23.334 --> 00:22:42.479
Go low, go slow inside. And that's what we do. It's very... and I learned that's what keeps you on balance.

00:22:42.480 --> 00:22:47.645
Do you want to read what the Lord said? Because he said it a lot better when you get it on recording.

00:22:47.646 --> 00:22:54.422
'Love, Diana.''Oh, I thought you said it perfect. You want me to still read it?''No. Did I say it perfect?''You said it beautiful.'Okay, love.

00:22:54.423 --> 00:23:10.479
I just want to make sure because I want to communicate it where people get this, because if you don't listen to what I'm telling you, I truly believe with all my heart that people won't make it in ministry, just like we've seen.

00:23:10.480 --> 00:23:31.509
And I keep trying to go and I want so bad for longevity, but not just longevity where you see mega-ministers with big houses, big cars, big planes, runways, whatever, with hundreds of millions in the bank, whatever TV program.

00:23:31.510 --> 00:23:40.479
Listen, folks, I'm just into him. The byproduct of following him is blessing. I get that.

00:23:40.480 --> 00:23:55.359
But where I'm at right now is I want that anointing so strong that whenever people see it, they see Jesus in me and they say, 'Brandon, what must I do to be saved?

00:23:55.360 --> 00:24:13.381
What must I do to be saved?'I am so broken that when my shadow passes by, the power of God radiates out of me so strong that they get healed by the Holy Ghost because the glory of the Lord is inside of me.

00:24:13.382 --> 00:24:27.918
Silver and gold have I none, but such as I have give I thee. I think about them all the time—the disciples—and they walked... they had been with Jesus.

00:24:27.919 --> 00:24:42.239
What does it take to stay with Jesus in these modern days with all these distractions, with all the social media and all these things, and you've got to get money and you've got to raise your kids and go to church?

00:24:42.240 --> 00:24:47.870
You've got all these things and all these voices, and I just keep the main thing the main thing.

00:24:47.871 --> 00:24:57.918
And it's like my friend Billy says—call him my mentor now, my spiritual father: 'Go vertical, Brandon.

00:24:57.919 --> 00:25:08.908
You must stay vertical and keep humble.'The longevity, even in your ministry, is to maintain humility in these last days.

00:25:08.909 --> 00:25:23.971
I always listen to him; maintain humility. There's so much arrogance and so much pride in people, and God resists the proud.

00:25:23.972 --> 00:25:33.455
He gives grace to the humble and in due time, he said he would exalt you. So, in humility...

00:25:33.456 --> 00:25:39.372
and I thought, is humility always just saying, 'It's not me, brother.

00:25:39.373 --> 00:25:45.663
I just want everybody to know it's all Jesus inside of me,'but inside you're just weak with arrogance?

00:25:45.664 --> 00:25:55.547
Because I see some people, they take pictures with their Gucci pants and they've got their stuff on there and they say, 'We just want to make the religious people squirm.'Arrogant, stinking...

00:25:55.548 --> 00:26:01.302
and you look at them with their big jet behind them. 'We just want to make the religious people squirm.'Arrogant?

00:26:01.303 --> 00:26:09.199
Are you kidding me? You're just full of pride, just oozing with pride, sir.

00:26:09.200 --> 00:26:17.199
And I already know what the Lord says about it. But I don't bust on people who have planes, but I do bust on arrogance.

00:26:17.200 --> 00:26:20.814
Regardless of whether you think you're not, it's arrogance.

00:26:20.815 --> 00:26:26.399
There are a lot of people who say, 'I'm not trying to brag,'but they're full of bragging.

00:26:26.400 --> 00:26:29.356
Full of bragging! That's all you're doing is just bragging about what you got.

00:26:29.357 --> 00:26:39.038
'$35 million.'You say you're not bragging? 'I'm not bragging, I'm just bragging on Jesus.'Okay, whatever.

00:26:39.039 --> 00:26:45.605
That's all you talk about: big houses, big cars. Because out of the abundance of the heart, the mouth speaks.

00:26:45.606 --> 00:26:49.992
'As a man thinketh in his heart, so is he.'What is more important?

00:26:49.993 --> 00:27:01.671
What are you always talking about? Souls. I'm going to be real with you. You know what my flex is going to be?

00:27:01.672 --> 00:27:12.844
When you say, 'I got a hundred million people saved.'A hundred million people got born again.

00:27:12.845 --> 00:27:21.980
Now, that's a flex. All glory to Jesus, though. I don't care. You could take your money and put it...

00:27:21.981 --> 00:27:31.278
I'm telling you, when I get on the other side and I'm standing before Jesus, I want him to say, 'Brandon, you did good, boy.

00:27:31.279 --> 00:27:36.588
You got a hundred million people saved, son.'It won't be, 'Brandon, you know what?

00:27:36.589 --> 00:27:44.639
You got a billion dollars in the bank. Well done.'He's not going to say that.

00:27:44.640 --> 00:27:55.199
'You believe me for that billion dollars and I saw that you had it in your bank account and I'm really impressed with that.'What does he care about the most?

00:27:55.200 --> 00:28:06.633
Souls. He died for every single one of you. When he looks at his hands and he shows them to me, and humongous holes were in them...

00:28:06.634 --> 00:28:19.274
humongous holes. He said, 'I suffered for you. I suffered for all of them.

00:28:19.274 --> 00:28:30.719
Would you help me bring in the harvest?'Brandon, that's my heart.

00:28:30.720 --> 00:28:36.319
My heart is the harvest, not how many zeros you have in your bank account.

00:28:36.320 --> 00:28:48.540
And there are so many pompous, arrogant preachers that I cannot stand to even watch because of how arrogant you are about your finances and all that you have and all that you bank up in your accounts.

00:28:48.541 --> 00:28:58.280
I hear about it and it's a stench before the body of Christ as you try to make excuses for everything you have.

00:28:58.281 --> 00:29:07.038
Billion-dollar homes, whatever... a million dollars. I don't care that you have it, but let's get the people saved.

00:29:07.039 --> 00:29:12.639
Jesus looks and he shows me his hands and he says, 'Look at my hands, Brandon.

00:29:12.640 --> 00:29:23.759
I died for every single one of them. Will you help me?'I know God's people will be blessed if you do right.

00:29:23.760 --> 00:29:27.992
When you give, it shall be given unto you: good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over.

00:29:27.993 --> 00:29:34.959
Will men give into your bosom. It's part of the spiritual law, but it's not where my focus is at.

00:29:34.960 --> 00:29:46.141
You've lost your focus. You've lost your first love. You fall in love with the world, you're an enemy of God.

00:29:46.142 --> 00:29:51.391
If you have fallen in love with the world, how can you say the things you say?

00:29:51.392 --> 00:30:01.839
"Well, you know, I'm trying to make people jealous, envious, stir up the religious spirits,"people say.

00:30:01.840 --> 00:30:08.428
I said, "Okay, but man, don't you want to stir up the body of the world?

00:30:08.429 --> 00:30:19.490
How do we bring people to Jesus? How do we have the nets?"I saw the big shrimping boats. I saw them full.

00:30:19.491 --> 00:30:30.573
And he said, "Brandon, I'm going to give you a big shrimping boat when it comes to souls now instead of this little boat you've had with the pole.

00:30:30.574 --> 00:30:37.780
You bring them in, but then you'll increase and there'll be shrimping boats all over the place."And I saw it.

00:30:37.781 --> 00:30:53.580
He said, "Just be faithful with what I've given you."But I've tried to tell you all as you look at the hands of Jesus, he died for every single one of you.

00:30:53.581 --> 00:31:07.999
And the Lord told me, "A lot of these ministers, their hearts are good, Brandon, but they've lost their reverence."Being reverent, they've lost it.

00:31:08.000 --> 00:31:28.239
Learn from their mistakes. I know we're all works in progress, but I so desperately want when I get over there for him to say, "You did good.

00:31:28.240 --> 00:31:42.479
You got a hundred million souls saved or whatever."And you said, "Now that's worth applauding."I hope that ministers to you tonight.

00:31:42.480 --> 00:31:49.514
I am so tired of the way people act and the more I'm around it, it's a stench to my nose.

00:31:49.514 --> 00:31:57.273
And you say, "Well, who cares what you think, Brandon?"Well, I so happen to hear the heart of the Father.

00:31:57.274 --> 00:32:09.003
I can hear it. As you walk prophetically, you hear what's on his heart and his heartbeat, and all that is around us. There's a lot of stench to his nose.

00:32:09.004 --> 00:32:17.553
